---
/**
 * Privacy Policy Page
 *
 * Stand for Hemp - Privacy policy for the advocacy platform
 */

import LandingLayout from '../layouts/LandingLayout.astro';
---

<LandingLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Stand for Hemp"
  description="Privacy policy for Stand for Hemp advocacy platform"
>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-24 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-reading">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-8" style="color: var(--color-soil-dark);">
        Privacy Policy
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 mb-8">
        <strong>Last Updated:</strong> November 2025
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed" style="color: var(--color-soil-dark);">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Our Commitment to Privacy
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            Stand for Hemp is a grassroots advocacy platform. We believe in transparency and protecting your privacy.
            This policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and your rights.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Information We Collect
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            We collect minimal information necessary to help you contact your representatives:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li><strong>Zip Code:</strong> Used to identify your congressional representatives</li>
            <li><strong>Contact Information:</strong> If you choose to send emails, we may collect your name and email address</li>
            <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Anonymous analytics about how people use the site (pages visited, time on site, etc.)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            How We Use Your Information
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            We use your information solely to facilitate advocacy:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>To connect you with your congressional representatives</li>
            <li>To send advocacy messages on your behalf (only when you explicitly request it)</li>
            <li>To improve the platform and measure campaign effectiveness</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mt-4">
            <strong>We never sell your information to third parties.</strong>
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Data Sharing
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            We only share your information when:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>You explicitly request to send messages to your representatives (your name and message will be sent to their offices)</li>
            <li>Required by law or legal process</li>
            <li>To protect the rights and safety of Stand for Hemp or others</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Cookies and Tracking
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            We use minimal cookies and tracking:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Essential cookies for site functionality</li>
            <li>Anonymous analytics to understand site usage</li>
            <li>No third-party advertising cookies</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Your Rights
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">
            You have the right to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
            <li>Access the personal information we have about you</li>
            <li>Request correction of inaccurate information</li>
            <li>Request deletion of your information</li>
            <li>Opt out of communications at any time</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Data Security
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information from unauthorized access,
            alteration, or destruction. However, no internet transmission is completely secure, and we cannot
            guarantee absolute security.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Children's Privacy
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            Our platform is not directed to children under 13, and we do not knowingly collect information
            from children under 13.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Changes to This Policy
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            We may update this privacy policy from time to time. We will notify users of significant changes
            by posting a notice on the website.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4" style="color: var(--color-hemp-green);">
            Contact Us
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-700">
            If you have questions about this privacy policy or our data practices, please contact us at:
            <br><strong>contact@standforhemp.com</strong>
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 text-center">
        <a href="/" class="btn-primary inline-block">
          ‚Üê Back to Home
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</LandingLayout>
